						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into the floor of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Veṅkaṭēśa Perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged and fragmentary. It belongs to the reign of a Rājakēsarivarman whose identity is not clear.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record an endowment for food offerings to god Tirumalai Āḻvār.</p>						

						</summary>
